Introduction

Park Min Hyuk, also known by his stage name Rocky, is a South Korean singer, rapper, songwriter, and actor signed under Wonijin Entertainment Entertainment Corp. (formerly ONE FINE DAY Entertainment).

He is a former member of the boy group ASTRO and the group's second duo sub-unit, JinJin & Rocky. On February 28, 2023, it was announced that Rocky had left ASTRO and Fantagio, as he had decided not to renew his contract.

On October 26, 2023, Rocky established his own agency under the name ONE FINE DAY Entertainment. However, on March 18, 2024, the company was officially rebranded as Wonijin Entertainment Corp., reflecting a fresh start and a new vision. He made his solo debut on November 22, 2023, with his first mini-album, "Rockyst."
